Compiling instructions: http://www.kdevelop.org/index.html?filename=HEAD/branches_compiling.html


KDevelop Platform API Documentation
-------------------------------------
API documentation is available from http://www.kdevelop.org/HEAD/doc/api/html/index.html

To build it by yourself, make sure you have KDE API documentation installed.
Run doxygen in the KDevelop top source directory to generate the API documentation.

If the KDE API documentation does not exist, it can be created
as follows:
  Install doxygen >= 1.5.0 and the fetch kdelibs sources. Then
  mkdir apidox
  cd apidox
  ../kdelibs/doc/api/doxygen.sh ../kdelibs/
  After that install kdelibs-apidocs directory to $KDEDIR/share/doc/HTML/en/
